President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Alabama and authorized federal aid to support recovery efforts after severe storms, flooding, tornadoes, and straight-line winds hit the area between April 10-13, 2009. The federal funding will be used for emergency work, repairing or replacing damaged facilities, and implementing hazard mitigation measures. Albert Lewis has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.